00:01:12.733 --> 00:01:15.387
In California, every county has the option

00:01:15.387 --> 00:01:18.183
to contract with a private agency

00:01:18.183 --> 00:01:21.191
to provide IHSS services to individuals

00:01:21.191 --> 00:01:24.400
who, for whatever reason,
can't manage their own work,

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:27.929
or don't have someone that they
want to be their caregiver,

00:01:27.929 --> 00:01:30.510
or have chronic substance abuse,

00:01:30.510 --> 00:01:35.023
mental health issues, also
developmental disabilities.

00:01:35.023 --> 00:01:37.610
One of the cornerstones at Homebridge

00:01:37.610 --> 00:01:39.306
is that we have always,

00:01:39.306 --> 00:01:43.155
since the organization began in 1994,

00:01:43.155 --> 00:01:44.934
provided training to our workers.

00:01:44.934 --> 00:01:46.626
We were committed, the board is committed,

00:01:46.626 --> 00:01:48.686
that the home care providers

00:01:48.686 --> 00:01:52.279
should be trained in understanding

00:01:52.279 --> 00:01:56.664
the needs of individuals
that require care.

00:01:56.664 --> 00:01:59.698
In 2010, the city and
county of San Francisco

00:01:59.698 --> 00:02:02.976
awarded Homebridge a contract
to expand our training,

00:02:02.976 --> 00:02:06.854
which Dennis actually
developed at the onset,

00:02:06.854 --> 00:02:08.443
to expand that training and offer it

00:02:08.443 --> 00:02:13.091
to all of the IHSS providers
in San Francisco County.

00:02:13.091 --> 00:02:16.693
There are about 20,000 recipients of IHSS

00:02:16.693 --> 00:02:19.180
in just the city and
county of San Francisco,

00:02:19.180 --> 00:02:22.751
and there are about 19,000
registered providers.

00:02:22.751 --> 00:02:24.462
So our trainings are available

00:02:24.462 --> 00:02:27.847
to all of those providers at no charge,

00:02:27.847 --> 00:02:29.963
and over the course of any given year

00:02:29.963 --> 00:02:32.604
we offer training to about 1,000 people,

00:02:32.604 --> 00:02:35.934
so we just kind of touch
on that surface of that.

